\begin_layout Subsection*
Intent to Treat Analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We start with an elaborate analysis of the Intent to Treat effects of the
 three technologies.
 For the first technology, video, we had virtually no household that refused
 to watch, and so the Intent to Treat effect is equivalent to the average
 treatment effect of the technology.
 This is not necessarily the case for the two other additional technologies.
 For instance, the IVR treatment consists of an encouragement to use the
 IVR system.
 We can not simply ignore the fact that a large proportion of farmers that
 were encouraged to use the IVR ended up not calling the system, as they
 are likely to be a non-random subset of the households that were assigned
 to the IVR treatment, leading to a biased estimate of the impact of the
 IVR technology.
 For instance, households that did not call may be lower educated than those
 that did call.
 Comparing average knowledge levels between groups who called the IVR and
 those that did not may reveal that the group that did not call has lower
 knowledge, yet it would be unclear if this is due to the fact that did
 not get information through the IVR or whether this is due to their lower
 level of education.
 Also for the third treatment, the SMS reminders, being allocated the treatment
 does not necessarily mean that the household also receives the SMS message.
 For instance, we have evidence that some messages did not reach the intended
 recipient.
 Also here, the probability that a particular household does not receive
 the intended treatment is likely non-random.
 For instance, households that live further away from a mobile phone tower
 may be more likely to experience technical issues leading to delays or
 non-delivery of the SMS message.
 Even though we feel that, from a policy perspective, the Intent to Treat
 analysis is the most informative, we also present additional analysis later
 in the article in an attempt to get a better estimate of the effectiveness
 of the different technologies itself.
 
\end_layout

